Invoking a Pipeline Thus far we have shown how to define stages and pipelines in MRO files. To run a pipeline, one writes a single pipeline call statement with a particular set of input arguments, into an MRO file. This is called an invocation. To invoke the example pipeline from above:
invoke.mro
@include &quot;pipeline.mro&quot; call DUPLICATE_FINDER( unsorted = &quot;/home/duplicator_dave/unsorted.txt&quot;, )  Typically, an invocation MRO file contains a single @include statement that includes the pipeline definition, and a single call statement.
